'''Trefi''' in [[Welsh language|Welsh]] or '''Trevi''' in [[English language|English]] is derived from the term for a person from the [[Trevethin]] area of [[South Wales]]. It is commonly used derogatorally, as [[chav]], [[townie]] or [[pikey]], but sometimes it is simply an abbreviation denoting a native of the town.

Although the town is not very big or populous, the term is fairly well-used in the surrounding areas. The inhabitants of trefethin are a cancer to wales and they are sick in the head man i is most definitley hating them 24/7. They are like chavs but ye but no but ye but no but ye they are turkey twizzlers in a frying pan. Like ghandi said turkey twizzlers go nice with bangers and mash. It is notably used by the pupils of [[Ysgol Gyfun Gwynllyw]], who come from other areas of South Wales, but the school is sited in Trevethin.

